{{Infobox royalty | title = Hereditary Princess of Hesse-Kassel | image = Lovisa Dorotea Sofia, 1680-1705, prinsessa av Preussen (Herman Hendrik Quiter d.y.) - Nationalmuseum - 15849.tif | name = Luise Dorothea of Prussia | house = [[House of Hohenzollern|Hohenzollern]] | spouse = {{marriage|[[Frederick I of Sweden|Frederick, Hereditary Prince of Hesse-Kassel]]|31 May 1700}} | birth_date = {{birth date|1680|9|29|df=y}} | death_date = {{death date and age|1705|12|23|1680|9|29|df=y}} | father = [[Frederick I of Prussia]] | birth_place = [[Stadtschloss, Berlin]] | mother = [[Elisabeth Henriette of Hesse-Kassel]] | death_place = [[Kassel, Germany|Kassel]] }} '''Princess Luise Dorothea of Prussia''' (Luise Dorothea Sophie; 29 September 1680 &ndash; 23 December 1705) was Hereditary Princess of Hesse-Kassel by marriage to [[Frederick I of Sweden|Frederick, Hereditary Prince of Hesse-Kassel]]. She was the daughter of [[Frederick I of Prussia|Frederick I]], [[King in Prussia|First King in Prussia]] by his first wife [[Elisabeth Henriette of Hesse-Kassel]]. She died in childbirth.
==Biography== {{House of Hohenzollern (Prussia)|frederick1}} On 31 May 1700, she married her first cousin [[Frederick I of Sweden|Frederick, Hereditary Prince of Hesse-Kassel]]. Frederick was King of Sweden 1720-1751 and [[Landgrave of Hesse-Kassel]] from 1730-1751.
Luise Dorothea was married in Berlin 31 May 1700 in a grand ceremony which took place during several weeks to great costs. [[Conrad Mel]] wrote ''Font Legatio orientalis'' at the occasion. During her five years of marriage, Luise Dorothea suffered from poor health. She died in childbirth.
Frederick remarried to [[Ulrika Eleonora of Sweden|Queen Ulrika Eleonora of Sweden]], becoming her prince consort and eventual King regnant of Sweden.
